<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="707" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 164.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In compliance with your instruction No.
                            92, of April 1, 1904, I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            forwarded to the Japanese minister at Berlin a list of Japanese
                            prisoners of war transmitted to me by the imperial ministry for foreign
                            affairs.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert S.
                            McCormick.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>